<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's set to take to ice in January for the new series of Dancing On Ice.</p>

<p>And Myleene Klass certainly had a spring in her step as she emerged for the first time since being for next year's star-studded lineup, to head to work at Smooth FM on Thursday.</p>

<p>The presenter, 42, cut a stylish figure in a black lace camisole and joggers as she strolled into Global Studios in London.</p>

<p>Happy: Myleene Klass, 42, cut a stylish figure as she emerged for the first time since being the first celebrity confirmed for Dancing On Ice 2021, to head to work at Smooth FM on Thursday</p>

<p>Myleene displayed her chic fashion sense by opting for the simple black lace camisole with a matching blazer as she strolled into the radio studios.</p>

<p>The mother-of-three teamed the look with comfy striped joggers and white trainers, as she headed to work on the afternoon radio show.</p>

<p>Myleene carried her essentials in a matching black handbag as she arrived to record the programme, after she became the first celebrity to be confirmed for Dancing On Ice 2021 on Sunday.</p>

<p>Lovely: The presenter looked chic in a black lace camisole and joggers as she strolled into Global Studios in London</p>

<p>Low-key: Myleene displayed her classy fashion sense by opting for the simple black lace camisole with a matching blazer as she strolled into the radio studios</p>

<p>Out and about: The mother-of-three teamed the look with comfy striped joggers and white trainers, as she headed to work on the afternoon radio show</p>

<p>She said that she's 'up for the challenge' and wants to make her daughters Ava, 13, and Hero, nine, 'proud'. </p>

<p>Myleene told her fans: 'Guess who won't be holding the coats at the side of the rink anymore! I am so, SO excited to be joining the cast of Dancing On Ice.</p>

<p>'My girls have always wanted me to do this but I've always been too scared someone will skate over my fingers!  </p>

<p>'Anyway, I want to make them proud and show them I'm up for a challenge when completely out of my comfort zone but most of all, I want a bum like Jlo!'    </p>

<p>Exciting: Myleene carried her essentials in a matching black handbag as she arrived to record the programme</p>

<p>Taking to the ice! It comes after she became the first celebrity to be confirmed for Dancing On Ice 2021 on Sunday</p>

<p>Determined: She said that she's 'up for the challenge' and wants to make her daughters Ava, 13, and Hero, nine, 'proud'</p>

<p>Myleene's exciting new challenge also comes just one week after she revealed she had gotten engaged to the father of her one-year-old son Apollo, Simon Motson.  </p>

<p>The mother-of-three was astounded when her partner of five years popped the question with a nine-carat diamond ring on the fifth anniversary of their first date. </p>

<p>Joining Myleene on the ice next year are stars including Denise Van Outen, Jason Donovan, Coronation Street's Faye Brooks and Emmerdale's Joe-Warren Plant. </p>

<p>Dancing On Ice will return to ITV in the new year and see twelve celebrities skate live with their professional partners each week.</p>

<p>The duos will try to impress both the panel and the viewers who will ultimately decide who is crowned the winner of the show.</p>

<p>Phillip Schofield and Holly Willoughby once again return to present the show and the expert panel of Torvill and Dean, John Barrowman and Ashley Banjo will all resume their roles as judges.</p>

<p>She's getting married! Myleene's exciting new challenge also comes just one week after she revealed she had gotten engaged to the father of her one-year-old son Apollo, Simon Motson</p>

